title: Want To Buy:  Dream AR
postcontent:
Dream AR Build

I'm Dave, a disabled veteran who enjoys target shooting, or as I call it; "Group Therapy." I have been working on my dream AR build; basically a fully automatic rifle just like the rifles carried by our brave men and women in the armed forces every day...and very much like the one I carried when I had the honor and privilege to serve in the U.S. Army. In short, building a fully automatic custom AR is quite expensive involving government laws, regulations and of course taxes, tariffs and fees. While doing research early one morning, since sleep eluded me once more and which just so happens to be Veteran's day, (HOOAH!), I stumbled up this website and figured why not?!?

Now I know there are A LOT more noble causes and better reasons to donate money and I'm not asking anyone to give who is anti-gun, or does not have a few dollars to throw this way toward this nut, but as always and especially if I succeed with this crazy endeavor, I invite all my family and friends to join me at the range and shoot this and every other firearm I own. Truth be told I am a little embarrassed I did this, but since I already linked it to my Facebook account and it posted an update on my timeline, I’m already committed!

So if you can; GREAT! If you can’t, wish me luck and for those of you that know me know I will document every step of this journey in writing and of course, with pictures. J  Please feel free to spread the word as I’m curious to see how many like-minded people there are out there.

If this works, I will definitely use this site again, but for one of those more noble causes I wrote about earlier in this early morning rambling. If you can donate to the cause, please email me via the link below.

Thanks for looking and for your donations.

DG

http://www.gofundme.com/group-therapy

title: Want To Buy:  Dream AR
postcontent:
Dream AR Build

I'm Dave, a disabled veteran who enjoys target shooting, or as I call it; "Group Therapy." I have been working on my dream AR build; basically a fully automatic rifle just like the rifles carried by our brave men and women in the armed forces every day...and very much like the one I carried when I had the honor and privilege to serve in the U.S. Army. In short, building a fully automatic custom AR is quite expensive involving government laws, regulations and of course taxes, tariffs and fees. While doing research early one morning, since sleep eluded me once more and which just so happens to be Veteran's day, (HOOAH!), I stumbled up this website and figured why not?!?

Now I know there are A LOT more noble causes and better reasons to donate money and I'm not asking anyone to give who is anti-gun, or does not have a few dollars to throw this way toward this nut, but as always and especially if I succeed with this crazy endeavor, I invite all my family and friends to join me at the range and shoot this and every other firearm I own. Truth be told I am a little embarrassed I did this, but since I already linked it to my Facebook account and it posted an update on my timeline, I’m already committed!

So if you can; GREAT! If you can’t, wish me luck and for those of you that know me know I will document every step of this journey in writing and of course, with pictures. J  Please feel free to spread the word as I’m curious to see how many like-minded people there are out there.

If this works, I will definitely use this site again, but for one of those more noble causes I wrote about earlier in this early morning rambling. If you can donate to the cause, please email me via the link below.

Thanks for looking and for your donations.

DG

http://www.gofundme.com/group-therapy

title: For Sale:  Browning BOSS A-Bolt 300 WIN MAG Leupold Scope
location: Santa Fe, New Mexico, United States
postcontent:
FS/FT Browning 300 WIN MAG A-Bolt Matte Black Stalker With BOSS system. Purchased new. Very Good Cond.  Have the BOSS wrench and standard recoil piece.  Leupold Vari X II 3-9X40 Scope with box and felt bag. Browning Rifle Soft Case, Browning Strap, I have a box or two of shells as well that go with it. This is an awesome big game setup; I just don’t hunt anymore and have no use for it. This thing was hitting right on at 100 yds  with a very tight group last time I shot it in 2009. Ready to hunt! The 300 WIN Mag is the most versatile big game rifle offering the most variety of bullet grains. Hunt Antelope with 165 Grain, Deer and Elk with 180 Grain or Moose a Grizzly with 220 Grain.  The 180 Grain makes this one of the best long range Calibers and bullet weight.  Winchester trajectory tables show that the 180 grain Power Point Plus bullet zeroed at 200 yards rises only 1.4" at 100 yards and falls just 6.4" at 300 yards. This is identical to the trajectory for the 130 grain Power Point Plus bullet in the famous .270 Winchester caliber. Obviously, Winchester's .300 is a fine long range big game cartridge.

The flip side of launching heavy bullets at high velocity is recoil, and abundant recoil is the dark side of all .300 Magnum cartridges. You can't cheat Mother Nature or the laws of physics.---The BOSS System Revolutionizes this though.  This 300 Win Mag has the kick of a 270 or lesser powered rifle thanks to the excellence of Browning's BOSS System. 

For those not familiar with Browning’s BOSS system. Ballistics Optimizing Shooting System is a fully adjustable muzzle break with settings for each specific brand and grain of shell. Allows you to fine tune your groupings to amazingly tight patterns.  For those who like the standard recoil of the 300 Win Mag, the standard recoil BOSS attachment is also included.

Asking $775 or Trade for SS 44 Mag revolver or SS 40 Cal Semi Auto Handgun.  Might take partial trade of other decent quality firearms.  I'm willing to seperate from the scope if desired.

I'm open to most trades.

location: Anywhere New York, New York, United States
postcontent:
Dream AR Build

I'm Dave, a disabled veteran who enjoys target shooting, or as I call it; "Group Therapy." I have been working on my dream AR build; basically a fully automatic rifle just like the rifles carried by our brave men and women in the armed forces every day...and very much like the one I carried when I had the honor and privilege to serve in the U.S. Army. In short, building a fully automatic custom AR is quite expensive involving government laws, regulations and of course taxes, tariffs and fees. While doing research early one morning, since sleep eluded me once more and which just so happens to be Veteran's day, (HOOAH!), I stumbled up this website and figured why not?!?

Now I know there are A LOT more noble causes and better reasons to donate money and I'm not asking anyone to give who is anti-gun, or does not have a few dollars to throw this way toward this nut, but as always and especially if I succeed with this crazy endeavor, I invite all my family and friends to join me at the range and shoot this and every other firearm I own. Truth be told I am a little embarrassed I did this, but since I already linked it to my Facebook account and it posted an update on my timeline, I’m already committed!

So if you can; GREAT! If you can’t, wish me luck and for those of you that know me know I will document every step of this journey in writing and of course, with pictures. J  Please feel free to spread the word as I’m curious to see how many like-minded people there are out there.

If this works, I will definitely use this site again, but for one of those more noble causes I wrote about earlier in this early morning rambling. If you can donate to the cause, please email me via the link below.

Thanks for looking and for your donations.

DG

http://www.gofundme.com/group-therapy
